Lenora Crichlow https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lenora_Crichlow 0 Lenora Isabella Crichlow (born 4 January 1985) is an English actress. She became known for her starring roles as Maria "Sugar" Sweet in the Channel 4 comedy-drama series Sugar Rush, Annie Sawyer in the BBC Three supernatural drama series Being Human, and Shania Andrews in the 2012 sports drama film Fast Girls. In 2013, Crichlow portrayed Chen Sam in the television film Burton Taylor. She has since had regular roles in the ABC sitcom Back in the Game and the NBC comedy series A to Z.
